track.name: Back Door Man
comments: This is Wille on vocal as well. There is a more famous version with Howlin' Wolf, but this ain't it. But great just the same. . .
Perfect! Howlin' Wolf on vocal Willie Dixon on double bass?
The unsung - to some - King of the Blues and architect of many rock and roll songs.  Jimmy Page and Robert Plant (Led Zeppelin) found out the hard way that you don't try to rob the King.
Mr. Chester Arthur Burnett, aka Howlin' Wolf, on vocals.
Willie is the most ripped-off songwriter in history - it's easy to see and hear why
Yeah, the door on the backside of your house of course : @
We all know what he means by backdoor man...
This version is Willie to be sure.
I think it's Howlin' Wolf on the vocals, it's great nevertheless! :)
